Where to Get Eclipse IDE for Java Web Developers
🌐 Official Download Website
https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/

Step-by-Step Download Guide
STEP 1: Go to Website
Open browser
Go to → https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
Click "Download x86_64" button

STEP 2: Click "Download" again
A mirror page opens
Click "click here" or "Download" button
It downloads "Eclipse Installer"

STEP 3: Run the Installer
Open downloaded file → eclipse-inst-jre-win64.exe
Installer window opens with multiple options
STEP 4: Choose the RIGHT Version ⚠️
You will see many options like:
❌ Eclipse IDE for Java Developers
❌ Eclipse IDE for C/C++ Developers
❌ Eclipse IDE for PHP Developers
✅ Eclipse IDE for Enterprise Java and Web Developers  ← SELECT THIS ONE

STEP 5: Install
Installation Folder : C:\Users\YourName\eclipse  (default is fine)
✅ Create Start Menu Entry
✅ Create Desktop Shortcut
Click "INSTALL"

STEP 6: Accept License
Click "Accept Now"
Wait for installation to complete

STEP 7: Launch
Click "LAUNCH"
Choose workspace folder → click Launch
Eclipse opens! ✅
⚠️ Before Installing Eclipse — Install Java JDK First!
Eclipse needs Java JDK to run!

Download JDK:
https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/
Download JDK 17 (LTS version — most stable)
Install it first
Then install Eclipse
💻 System Requirements
Thing	Minimum
OS	Windows 10/11, Mac, Linux
RAM	4GB minimum (8GB recommended)
Storage	2GB free space
Java	JDK 17 or above
📥 Direct Download Link
What	Link
Eclipse Official	https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
JDK 17 (Oracle)	https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/
JDK 17 (Free - OpenJDK)	https://adoptium.net/
✅ Adoptium (OpenJDK) is completely free and works perfectly!

Installation Order (Do This Order Only!)
1️⃣  Download & Install JDK 17 first
        ↓
2️⃣  Download Eclipse Installer
        ↓
3️⃣  Run Installer → Choose "Enterprise Java and Web Developers"
        ↓
4️⃣  Launch Eclipse
        ↓
5️⃣  Install Spring Tools 4 plugin (for Spring Boot)
        ↓
6️⃣  Start coding REST API! 🚀
🔌 After Eclipse Opens — Install Spring Tools Plugin
Help → Eclipse Marketplace
  → Search "Spring Tools"
  → Install "Spring Tools 4"
  → Restart Eclipse
Now you can create Spring Starter Project and build REST APIs! ✅
